<FIRST>r a AM-CocaineCache     10-04 0182</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Cocaine Cache,0186</SECOND>
<HEAD>Law Officers Seize Nine-Ton Cocaine Cache</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARLINGEN, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities seized almost 18,000 pounds
of cocaine Wednesday in what could be the second-largest amount in
U.S. history and arrested five people, officials said.
   ``We think it's the second-largest cocaine seizure in the U.S.,
second only to the 40,000 pounds seized last week in (Los
Angeles),'' said Mike Cox, a spokesman for the state Department of
Public Safety in Austin.
   The 17,950 pounds of cocaine _ nearly nine tons _ were seized
and the five were arrested fat a rural residence just west of
Harlingen, said DPS Sgt. Tony Garcia.
   Seven men were arrested last week in Los Angeles and Las Vegas
after a record 20-ton cocaine seizure connected to the Mexican leg
of a major smuggling operation that brought the drug from Colombia.
   Federal investigators have linked a warehouse in El Paso and
three homes across the border in Ciudad Juarez to the Los Angeles
cocaine stash. Drug agents said the cocaine apparently came into
the country via El Paso and was then shipped to Los Angeles.
</TEXT>
