<FIRST>r i PM-Israel-Lebanon     10-04 0126</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Israel-Lebanon,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Israelis Kill Two Guerrillas In Lebanon</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Israeli soldiers killed two guerrillas in a
firefight in Israel's self-proclaimed security zone in southern
Lebanon, and one soldier was slightly hurt, an army spokesman said.
   He said Tuesday's clash occurred nearly two miles north of the
border, in a deep, vegetation-covered ravine near the Lebanese
Shiite Moslem village of Bayt Lif.
   The spokesman, speaking anonymously under army regulations, said
a patrol encountered a guerrilla group at close range and attacked
it.
   It was not immediately clear whether more than two guerrillas
were involved or to which organization they belonged.
   Israel carved out the six-to-10 mile security zone when it
withdrew the bulk of its troops from Lebanon in 1985 following a
three-year occupation.
