<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0488</SECOND>
<HEAD>Snow in Western Mountains; Windy, Cool in Northeast</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Windy and unseasonably cool weather persisted in the Northeast
today, while light snow was expected on top of at least 6 inches
that covered mountain passes in Idaho and Montana.
   Early morning temperatures were in the 30s and 40s from New
England to Pennsylvania and across the Great Lakes to the northern
Plains.
   Gale warnings were in effect today for Lake Ontario and
small-craft advisories were posted along the Atlantic coast. Clouds
covered much of the Northeast, with showers likely and snow showers
possible in higher elevations.
   In the West, Monida Pass along the Montana-Idaho border reported
6 inches of snow at mid-afternoon Tuesday, and West Yellowstone,
Mont., reported a cover of five inches. Light snow continued
falling into the night.
   The upper-level weather disturbance responsible for the snow
also produced strong winds across parts of Arizona and Nevada, with
gusts as high as 38 mph at Kingman and Winslow, Ariz., Tuesday
afternoon.
   Scattered showers and a few thunderstorms extended from southern
Arizona across northern New Mexico into Colorado Tuesday evening,
and it rained this morning in lower elevations in Montana.
   It was cloudy this morning across much of the Plateau and Rocky
Mountain region into the northern and central High Plains.
   Fair skies prevailed across the rest of the nation.
   Tuesday's high temperature in the Lower 48 states was 98 degrees
at Presidio, Texas, while Miami, at 92, tied a record high set in
1977.
   Other reports:
   _East: Albany, N.Y. 41 showery; Atlanta 61 fair; Boston 44 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 70 fair; Chattanooga 57 fair; Cincinnati 43 fair;
Cleveland 45 partly cloudy; Detroit 34 fair; Hatteras 68 fair;
Jacksonville 69 foggy; Key West 82 fair; Knoxville 52 fair; Macon
60 fair; Miami 77 fair; New York 50 fair; Philadelphia 45 fair;
Pittsburgh 41 fair; Portland, Maine 42 fair; Richmond 53 fair.
   _Central: Birmingham 59 fair; Bismarck 38 partly cloudy; Chicago
39 fair; Denver 44 cloudy; Des Moines 39 fair; Little Rock 59 fair;
Louisville 50 fair; Memphis 60 fair; Nashville 54 fair; New Orleans
68 foggy; North Platte 48 cloudy; Oklahoma City 56 fair; Omaha 35
fair; Rapid City 46 cloudy; St. Louis 48 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul
31 fair; Sault Ste. Marie 39 partly cloudy; San Antonio 77 partly
cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 59 showery; Anchorage 50 cloudy; Boise 47
cloudy; Casper 37 fair; Fairbanks 45 cloudy; Great Falls 36 rain;
