<HEAD>Men Fail to Open Bank Safe, Getaway Car Crashes; Suspect Captured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three men with an M-16 rifle, a
grenade, a pistol and a knife robbed a bank, but police captured
one suspect after he rammed a stolen car into several other
vehicles, authorities said today.
   Lt. Col. Supavith Chuunak said the three entered a branch of the
Thai Farmers Bank at midday Tuesday shouting ``This is a robbery''
and firing warning shots.
   Supavith said the robbers tried to open the bank safe but
failed. They fled the bank with $4,000 from the bank counter and
customers.
   According to the police account, one man ran from the bank
wielding the M-16 and tried to steal a car outside the bank.
   The car owner fought the man, wresting away the M-16 before the
suspect drove off with the car.
   About a half mile from the scene, the car crashed into at least
four cars and stalled. The suspect tried to run away, but
passers-by, thinking he was trying to flee the scene of an
accident, grabbed and held him police arrived.
   The other suspects remained at large.
