<HEAD>Dow Jones Hits All-Time High</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices climbed to an all-time high, buoyed
by optimism over interest rates.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 40.84 Tuesday to
close at 2,754.56. That topped the widely-followed barometer's
previous high of 2,752.09, reached Sept. 1. Broader market
indicators also hit new highs.
   Advancing issues outnumbered declining ones by about 2 to 1 in
nationwide trading of New York Stock Exchange-listed stocks. Volume
on the floor of the Big Board was a heavy 182.55 million shares.
   Analysts said investors were optimistic the Federal Reserve
might relax credit further, given relatively slow economic growth
and no sign of increasing inflationary pressure. Strength in the
dollar also bolstered stock prices.
   The most actively traded issue on the NYSE was USX, which jumped
1] to 36\ amid speculation that financier Carl Icahn was adding to
his 11.4 percent stake.
   Boeing was up 3[ to 59} as the company's Machinists voted on
whether to accept a new contract or strike at midnight. After the
market closed, it was announced the Machinists had decided to
strike.
