<FIRST>r a PM-BRF--BuildingDeath     10-04 0121</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Building Death,0123</SECOND>
<HEAD>Falling Construction Weight Kills Man</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 56-pound weight fell from a building's
17th-floor scaffolding and hit a court officer in the head, killing
him, authorities said.
   Sgt. John Dauway, 48, was the second person killed by an object
falling from the office building in the Brooklyn Heights section. A
lawyer was killed in 1982 by a chunk of decorative terra cotta that
fell from the 16th floor.
   The weight that hit the 19-year state Supreme Court officer had
anchored a scaffold and beam that held construction pulleys. The
building was being renovated.
   Construction worker Sammy Santiago said he saw the weight fall,
miss the protective structure erected over the sidewalk and hit
Dauway.
</TEXT>
