<HEAD>Pakistani Sailors Rescued By Indians In Gulf</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUBAI, United Arab Emirates (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eight Pakistani sailors were
rescued by an Indian crew after jumping into the Persian Gulf to
escape their flaming cargo ship, the vessel's owners said Wednesday.
   The wooden 450-ton Jameel was gutted by the blaze, its owner,
Sultan Ahmed Hareb, said.
