picked up the sailors Tuesday, 12 hours after the Jameel caught
fire, Hareb said. It brought them to the southern gulf port of
Dubai.
   The fire broke out after the Dubai-registered Jameel experienced
engine problems in the Gulf of Oman. It was returning home with a
cargo of fertilizer and onions from Karachi.
   The U.A.E. coast guard was expected to start a search Wednesday
for the remains of the $400,000 vessel, Hareb said.
