<HEAD>Bright &amp; Brief</HEAD>
<DATELINE>QUAKERTOWN, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police can't find the owner of a 4-foot,
fiberglass squirrel that appeared on a football field, but they
suspect the animal is a fugitive from a miniature golf course.
   The hollow figure dubbed Squinky showed up Monday on the 50-yard
line of a school playing field. Police and school officials figure
it was a prank, but they can't find anyone to claim the squirrel.
   Police have been calling miniature golf courses to no avail. The
search for Squinky's owner continued Wednesday.
