<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Soviet-Nuclear     10-04 0098</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Soviet-Nuclear,0101</SECOND>
<HEAD>Soviets Stage Underground Nuclear Test</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Soviet Union exploded a nuclear bomb
underground in Central Asia on Wednesday as part of a program to
modernize its military technology, the official news agency
reported.
   The device had a yield of up to 20 kilotons, Tass said in its
brief dispatch.
   Twenty kilotons, or the force of 20,000 tons of TNT, was the
yield of the atomic bomb dropped by the United States on Hiroshima,
Japan, in 1945.
   The Soviet nuclear blast took place at the test range of
Semipalatinsk in the Kazakhstan Republic.
</TEXT>
