<HEAD>Cadence To Buy Gateway Design Of Lowell, Mass.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Cadence Design Systems Inc. has agreed
to buy Gateway Design Automation Corp. of Lowell, Mass., in a stock
exchange valued at more than $72 million.
   San Jose-based Cadence, a growing supplier of software for the
design of integrated circuits, reported sales of $67.1 million last
year.
   Gateway has specialized in software for the simulation of
circuits and testing of electronic designs. Cadence had earlier
this year entered a cooperative marketing agreement with Gateway
and had offered Gateway's simulation software as part of its
overall line of products for electronic design.
   Cadence said Gateway will operate as a division under Prabhu
Goel, Gateway's founder, president and chief executive. Goel will
also serve on the board.
   Cadence said it will issue 4 million shares of stock to buy
Gateway. The merger will increase Cadene's workforce from 750 to
about 900 people. Cadence said it hopes to complete the
consolidation by year's end.
   The merger must still be approved by regulatory agencies and
Gateway stockholders.
